line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.25in;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-.25in'><b><span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>1.1<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp; </span></span></b><b><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> Introduction
and background</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The Public Service
must be accountable for its performance and the services it provides, in order
to facilitate the attainment of the national vision and objectives. In that
regard, a number of reforms aimed at enhancing the performance and
accountability of public service organizations have been initiated and
implemented. One of the key strategies for this is strengthening a joint
approach to inspections and performance measurement. <span style='color:black'>Government
Institutions have to be inspected regularly and their performance has to be
rated periodically in order to identify and implement strategies for continuous
improvement in the quality of public services. This requires
institutionalizing a mechanism for rewarding Institutions that deliver excellent
services and putting in place measures for improvement in those institutions
that underperform. The rating of performance is also expected to promote
healthy competition and innovation among Institutions in delivering quality and
timely services to the citizens.</span> <span style='color:black'>To that
effect, a Performance Measurement Tool for Ministries, Departments, Agencies
(MDAs) and Local Governments (LGs) known as the Performance Scorecard, has been
developed as an Inspection Tool to drive continuous improvements in the quality
of services delivered to the citizens.</span></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>These are
guidelines for Inspection and Performance Assessment of Ministries,
Departments, Agencies (MDAs), Local Governments (LGs) and service delivery
facilities. The Guidelines provide a framework for a coordinated approach to
support supervision, inspection, quality assurance and performance
assessment. They cover key areas under the Performance Scorecard and sector
specific inspection issues. Each MDA has the responsibility to set performance
and service delivery standards and to implement projects and programmes for the
attainment of institutional, sector and national objectives. Every MDA should
therefore be subjected to an inspection and performance assessment exercise to
ascertain the extent to which it conforms to the set objectives and standards.
In addition, each MDA has the responsibility to provide technical support and
inspect local governments in the areas of their respective mandates. In view
of the increasing number of local governments and limited resources, financial,
personnel and tools and equipment, the coverage of inspection by central
government agencies is limited and hence not effective. At the same time, there
are inefficiencies in time and cost arising from different inspectors travelling
to the same local governments at different times. Worse still, there is no
mechanism to share inspection findings and ensure follow up action is taken to
implement recommendations in order to improve the delivery of public services.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:150%'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>These Guidelines have
been developed as an instrument for institutionalizing the performance
scorecard and conducting joint inspections.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
150%'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>1.2 <b>Purpose
of the Guidelines </b></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:
.5in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The
purpose of these guidelines is to:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.75in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;
line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>a)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Promote a joined
up approach to inspections of MDAs, local governments and service delivery
facilities. </span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.75in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;
line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>b)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Provide a standard
and consistent approach to MDAs and LGs in the implementation of the
Performance Scorecard. </span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.75in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;
line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>c)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Provide
opportunities for identifying and addressing key issues that have a great
impact on performance and service delivery by the public sector.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.75in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;
line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>d)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Rank the
performance of MDAs, LGs, and service delivery facilities.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
150%'>&nbsp;</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
150%'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>1.3 <b>Rationale
for Joint Inspections</b></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>A joined approach
to inspection of MDs, LGs and service delivery facilities is being promoted in
order to: </span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.75in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;
line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>a)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Institutionalize
performance assessment against service delivery standards using the performance
scorecard.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.75in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;
line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>b)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Provide for a
coordinated approach to planning and execution of inspection.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.75in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;
line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>c)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Standardize and
professionalize the inspection practice and process.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.75in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;
line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>d)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Increase coverage
of facilities, local governments and issues that are inspected.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.75in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;
line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>e)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Increase
efficiency gains in terms of cost, human resources and time for both the
inspectors and those inspected.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.75in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;
line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>f)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Improve the focus
of inspection on issues that directly affect performance and service delivery.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.75in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;
line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>g)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Collectively
identity and address performance and service delivery gaps.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.75in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;
line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>h)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Strengthen the
incentive and sanction framework for compliance to performance and service
delivery standards.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.75in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:150%'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>
</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;
line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>1.4 <b>Application
of the Performance Scorecard</b></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormalCxSpLast style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
0in;margin-left:.5in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The
Performance Scorecard is an institutional Performance Measurement instrument
for Ministries, Departments, Agencies (MDAs) and Local Governments (LGs) that
is applied as an Inspection Tool to drive continuous improvements in the
quality of services delivered to the citizens, based on the balanced scorecard.
</span><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The
balanced scorecard approach supports organizational </span><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>focus on strategy
and results, ensuring that organizational performance is improved by measuring
what really matters. It also aligns organizational strategy with the work
employees undertake on a day-to-day basis, taking into account the drivers of
future performance. </span><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The
objectives of the performance scorecard are to:</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.5in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>a)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Rate the performance of MDAs and LGs regarding the provision of
public services.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.5in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>b)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Provide a framework for reward and recognition of MDAs and LGs
that demonstrate high standards of performance and continuous improvement in
the quality of public services.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:0in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.5in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>c)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Promote policies, strategies, best practices and innovative
initiatives to improve performance management and service delivery processes
and approaches; and,</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:0in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.5in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>d)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Encourage healthy competition among MDAs and LGs for the efficient
and effective management and delivery of public services. </span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;
line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>1.5 <b>Principles
and core values for implementation of the Performance Scorecard</b></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;
line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>1.5.1 <b>Principles
for the Performance Scorecard</b></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.75in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;
line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>a)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><b><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Leadership for
performance management and service delivery:</span></b><span style='font-size:
12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> every political and chief
executive officer of an MDA or LG will take responsibility for the performance
of the organization and demonstrate the required commitment to continuous
performance improvement.</span></p>

