<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;
line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>1.7 <b>Procedure
for conducting a Performance Assessment</b></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The
Performance Scorecard has been designed as an inspection tool. In that regard,
performance assessment will be linked to the inspection process. This will
involve </span><span lang=EN-GB style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>internal review within the MDA or LG</span><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>
and an external inspection process through the joint approach to inspection. </span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:
justify;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-GB style='font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>1.7.1 <b>Internal assessment process
within</b></span><b><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>
an MDA or LG</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:
justify;text-indent:.5in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Each MDA or LG will be expected to
undertake the following:</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>a)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Clearly
outlining its strategic vision and direction:</span></b><span lang=MS
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'> It is
important for every MDA or LG to obtain a common uderstanding </span><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>regarding
what the organisation is about, what it really does and how it contributes to
the overall national vision. This vision should be articulated in a strategic
plan and client charter.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>b)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Defining
key result areas:</span></b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif'> each MDA or LG should define key result areas that
should form the basis for the annual policy statement and annual budget and
performance plan.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:0in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>c)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Defining
business systems and processes:</span></b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> manual or computerised business systems
and processes should be clearly defined and service recipients informed of the
steps they need to take in order to obtain a service.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>d)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Maintaining
performance data:</span></b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif'> performance data should be maintained based on the
quarterly and annual performance reports and individual staff performance appraisal
system.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>e)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Notification for inspection:</span></b><span lang=MS
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'> the
Chief Eexcutive of each MDA or LG will recieve a notification for inspection as
per the programme, once every two years, at least one month before the physical
inspection. </span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>f)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Distributing criteria to all Departments:</span></b><span lang=MS
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'> the
notification for inspection and the performance assessment criteria should be
distributed to all Heads of Department to enable them make adequate preparation
for the exercise. This will mainly include the Inspection Manual, the
Gudielines for performance assessement and any other documents that may be
relevant. </span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>g)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Assigning/appointing an Officer to be in charge of the process: </span></b><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>the
Chief Executive Officer should identify a competent Officer at Senior Level to
support the coordination of the exercise. Each Department or Unit should also
identify an Officer to coordinate the exercise within the Department.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>h)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Internal Departmental review/preparatory meetings:</span></b><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>
each Departmental Head should hold an internal meeting to review its
performance and to respond to issues raised in the Performance Assessment and Inspection
Manual. </span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>i)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Organizational Review Meeting: </span></b><span lang=MS
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>the
Chief Executive Officer should organize an insitutional level meeting to
discuss the overall performance of the MDA or LG. Political leadership of the
MDA or LG should be invited to chair such a meeting. Each Department or Unit
should make a presentation of its performance,after which the MDA or LG should undertake
a comprehensive assessment of its performance, using Form A and B of the
Performance Assessment. </span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>j)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Collecting documentary evidence to support the assessment of each
cirteria:</span></b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'> Departmental focal officers should collect evidence within their
Department or Unit. The evidence should be consolidated by the MDA or LG
overall coordinator of the assessement programme.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>k)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Being available for the inspection programme:</span></b><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>
Senior Managment and all Heads of Department should be available during the
physical inspection programme in order to provide any additional information or
clarification that may be sought, and to obtain feedback from the team of
inspectors.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>l)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Assessment of performance of an MDA or LG: </span></b><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>the
assessment of an MDA or LG will be agreed to at the end of the inspection
exercise and will be supported by the available evidence provided and the findings
at the time of inspection. </span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:0in;text-align:justify;line-height:
150%'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:0in;text-align:justify;line-height:
150%'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=EN-GB
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>1.7.2 <b>External
assessment process </b></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:
.5in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>The external assessment process will comprise ten (10) phases
namely:</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>a)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Planning and budgeting:</span></b><span lang=MS style='font-size:
12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'> Ministry of Public
Service, together with other key inspectorate agencies will agree an annual
inspection and performance assessment programme at the begging of each
financial year. The programme will be communicated to all MDAs and LGs to
enable them make adequate preparation for the exercise.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>b)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Notification for the inspection exercise:</span></b><span lang=MS
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>
letters of notification and necessary documents will be sent to MDAs and LGs as
per the programme to enable them adequate preparation for the exercise.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>c)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Constitution of inspection teams:</span></b><span lang=MS
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>
inspection teams will be constituted to undertake the physical inspection/evaluation
of the performance of MDAs and LGs. The teams will comprise membership from a
cross-section of inspection agencies.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>d)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>De-briefing the inspection teams:</span></b><span lang=MS
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'> a
meeting of the inspection team should take place to prepare for the executtion
of the inspection programme. The meeting should identify outstanding issues,
and prepare the materials.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>e)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Briefing leadership and top management of MDAs and LGs:</span></b><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>
the inspection team will secure the inspection exercise as per the programme.
The team will brief the top leadership and managment regarding the purpose of
the inspection and performance assessment exercise, the programme and the
required supporting information/documents to be used. Give examples </span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>f)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Physical inspection/verification:</span></b><span lang=MS
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'> the
inspection team will undertake an on-sight inspection/evaluation of the
performance and service delivery standards, including the performance report, procedures,
processes, records, stores and premises. Service delivery facilities that
include health facilities, schools, water points, roads, plant and animal
clinics etc., will be inspected. The team will meet each Department/Unit seperately
as will be required. The team will conduct an assessment based on the criteria
and on the physical performance report on key result areas. </span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>g)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Review of documents and reports:</span></b><span lang=MS
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'> the
team will review documents and reports to validate the physical inspection
findings.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>h)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Meeting with middle managment and support staff:</span></b><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>
the team will hold a separate meeting with middle management and support staff.
This is necessary in order to obtain an overall picture of what transpires in
the organization, to take into account the different expereinces of top management
and support staff.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>i)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Focus
Group Discussion:</span></b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif'> where necessary and approriate, the
inspection/assessment team shall conduct a focus group discussion with a
cross-section of staff, opinion leaders, service recipients and other
stakeholders. Representation from NGOs and Civil Society operating in the local
area or in partnership with an MDA or LG should be invited to participate in
the discussion.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>j)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>De-briefing session: </span></b><span lang=MS style='font-size:
12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>at the end of the
inspection exercise, the team will meet top management for an exit briefing and
share inspection findings. A joint performance assessment will be made and
agreed to, based on the internal assesment of the institution and the
assessment of the inspection team. The assessment will be supported by
documentary or other physical evidence, guided by the honest need for
performance and service delivery improvement. </span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:0in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:0in;text-align:justify'><b><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>1.7.3 Declaration
of the results and recognition of performance</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:0in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>
</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>a)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Writing inspection reports:</span></b><span lang=MS
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'> the
inspection team will prepare detailed inspection reports and collate the
inspection results and share the findings amongst the joint technical
committee/inspection team to harmonise the results/findings.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>b)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Presentation of inspection results to the Steering Committee on
inspection:</span></b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'> the Department of Inspection, that constitutes the Secretariat of
the Steering Committee will present the inspection results to the Steering
Committee and other emerging issues that require to be drawn to the attention
of the committee. The Steering Committee shall be chaired by the Head of the
Public Service and Secretary to Cabinet, and shall comprise Permanent
Secretaries of the inspection MDAs. Upon endorsement of the results by the
Steering Committee, the results will be announced to the respectiveMDAs and LGs
as well as recommendations for improvement. </span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>c)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Recognizing and rewarding performance:</span></b><span lang=MS
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'> an annual
event to recognize and reward performance shall be held.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>d)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Performance improvement:</span></b><span lang=MS style='font-size:
12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'> follow up actions to
improve performance shall be agreed to and undertaken by the respective
institutions before the next inspection and assesment exercise.</span><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> </span><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;
line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>1.8 <b>Institutional
Arrangements for implementation of the Performance Scorecard</b></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='text-align:justify'><span lang=MS
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The
institutional arrangments for the implementation of the Performance Scorecard
broadly include the following:</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>a)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Steering Committee of Inspection Agencies/Awards committee:</span></b><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>
this shall be chaired by the Head of Public Service and Secretary to Cabinet.
The committee shall comprise Permanent Secretaries of the inspection agencies.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>b)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Technical Committee on inspection/assessment committee:</span></b><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>
this shall include technical officers from the inspection agencies. It shall in
effect constitute the Assessment Panel and shall be chaired by the Director
responsible for inspection.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>c)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Secretariat to the Steering Committee and Technical Committee of
inspection:</span></b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'> this shall be the Department of Inspection of the Ministry of
Public Service, headed by the Commissioner for Inspection.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>d)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Chief Executive Officer/Accounting Officer of an MDA or LG:</span></b><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>
This shall be Permanent Secretary, or Chief Administrative Officer, or Town
Clerk or Executive Director. He/She shall take leadership and responsiblity for
the internal assessemnt process, performance results and for implementation of
recommendations.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:-.25in'><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>e)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Focal Point Officer:</span></b><span lang=MS style='font-size:
12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'> each MDA or LG shall
identify/asign a Focal Point Officer who shall be responsible for the internal
coordination of the exercise. </span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;
line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>1.9 <b>Uses of
Inspection and Performance Assessment Results</b></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-.25in'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>a)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><b><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Reward
and recognition:</span></b><span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> the Performance Scorecard </span><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>provides
leverage for comparing performance of institutions: It makes it possible to
compare the performance of MDAs and LGs and thereby provide a basis for
rewarding and sanctioning institutional performance, and subsequently promoting
healthy competition amongst MDAs and LGs.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-.25in'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>b)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><b><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Performance
improvement: </span></b><span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>the </span><span lang=EN-GB
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Performance
Scorecard identifies performance gaps and helps MDAs and LGs to prioritise and
focus on the key areas for performance improvement.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-.25in'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>c)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><b><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Planning
and budgeting:</span></b><span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> results from the assessment shall inform
the planning and budgeting process and identify priorities where MDAs and LGs
may place additional resources.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-.25in'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>d)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><b><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Policy
management:</span></b><span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> results from the inspection findings and
performance measurement shall help to identify areas where policy review is
required, or where new policy needs to be put in place. Cabinet and Parliament
shall be regularly informed regarding the policy implications of the inspection
findings. </span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><b><span style='font-size:12.0pt;
line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>1.10 Expected benefits
for applying the Performance Scorecard as an inspection tool</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-.25in'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>a)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><b><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Complimenting
other Performance Management Instruments:</span></b><span lang=EN-GB
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>
the Performance Scorecard compliments other performance management instruments
like ROM, client charters, Output Oriented Budgeting (OOB), performance
agreements and staff performance appraisal. </span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-.25in'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>b)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><b><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Improving
citizen participation and trust in Government:</span></b><span lang=EN-GB
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>
Performance Scorecard provides a mechanism for citizen participation in public
service delivery and thereby contributes to increasing trust in Government
services and creating a positive image of the public service.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-.25in'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>c)<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><b><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Enhancing
the relationship between organisational performance and whole of government
approach:</span></b><span lang=EN-GB style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> the Performance Scorecard shall promote the
whole of Government approach as an integrated system, and the connectedness of
the public service delivery chain and outcomes.</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:0in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>1.11 <b>Frequency
of Performance Assessment</b></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='text-align:justify'><span lang=MS
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The
Performance Scorecard will be applied after every two years, in accordance with
planned inspection programmes. A one year period shall be provided to an MDA or
LG to implement the recommendations of the inspection findings before another
assesement is carried out. Within a financial year, assessment shall be
scheduled and undertaken on a quaterly basis. </span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:0in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:0in;text-align:justify'><span
lang=MS style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>1.12 <b>Application
of the Guidelines</b></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The
Performance Assessment and Inspection Manual shall be applied whenever a team
of inspectors is constituted to conduct an inspection of an MDA, LG or service
delivery facility and to administer the Performance Scorecard. Such a team
shall always comprise appropriate level of expertise from the MDAs undertaking
such an inspection. These Guidelines shall also be applied by each MDA, LG or
service delivery facility in preparation for a joint inspection and performance
assessment exercise. Where an MDA wishes to conduct an inspection separately,
such an MDA shall apply its own separate inspection manual/instruments.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormalCxSpMiddle style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.5in'><b>2.0 </b><b><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Performance
Scorecard Assessment Format and Sub-criteria</span></b></p>

