of the Inspection and Performance Assessment Exercise</b></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify'><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>As part of the inspection and
performance assessment process, the inspectors will be required to obtain
feedback from the institution inspected regarding the general management and
conduct of the exercise, and the benefits derived from the inspection and the
performance assessment, as experienced by the organization inspected. </span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>5.0 <b>Declaration</b></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Inspectors
will initial the inspection and assessment Reports to confirm that physical
inspection was undertaken and that the findings were drawn to the attention of
the agency inspection in advance. </span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:
justify;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>6.0 <b>Conclusion
</b></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>In
conformity with these Guidelines, all Government Ministries, Departments,
Agencies and Local Governments are now required to be inspected against the
Institutional Performance Scorecard in order to promote the efficient and
effective delivery of public services and subsequently economic growth and
poverty reduction. Pilot implementation of the Performance Scorecard was done
during 2014/15. Lessons learnt from the pilot will inform the roll out to all
Ministries, Departments and Agencies (MDAs) and Local Government (LGs).</span></p>

